<function>

access:   public

name: __call

param: string, $method

param: array, $params

return: void

</function>

Magic shorthand for saving an event using a method name.

* Parameters:

 * string //$method//: The event type.

 * array //$params//: Additional parameters; only the first paramter is used (the message to log).

* Returns void

<code type="php">
// these are equivalent:
$log->save('info', 'informational message');
$log->info('informational message');
</code>